  "prompt": "How do I use the desktop version of Instagram?",
  "response": "The \"desktop version\" of Instagram refers to accessing Instagram through a web browser on your computer, rather than using the mobile app. Here's how you can use Instagram on your desktop:\n\n---\n\n### **Steps to Use Instagram on Your Desktop:**\n\n1. **Open a Web Browser:**\n   - Use a browser like Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox, Safari, or Microsoft Egde.\n\n2. **Go to Instagram's Website:**\n   - Visit [www.instagram.com](https://www.instagram.com).\n\n3. **Log In to Your Account:**\n   - Enter your username (or email/phone number) and password to log in.\n   - If you don\u2019t have an account, you can create one by clicking \"Sign Up.\"\n\n4. **Navigate the Interface:**\n   - **Home Feed:** View posts from accounts you follow.\n   - **Explore:** Discover new content by clicking the magnifying glass icon.\n   - **Search:** Look for accounts, hashtags, or locations using the search bar.\n   - **Profile:** Click on your profile picture to access your profile, where you can edit your bio, view your posts, or switch accounts.\n\n5. **Interact with Content:**\n   - **Like:** Double-click a post or click the heart icon below it.\n   - **Comment:** Click the speech bubble icon below a post to add a comment.\n   - **Share:** Click the paper plane icon to send a post via Direct Message.\n\n6. **Upload Posts (Limited Functionality):**\n   - Instagram's desktop version has limited post-uploading capabilities. To upload posts or stories, you\u2019ll need to use the mobile app.\n   - However, you can upload images by enabling \"Developer Tools\" in your browser or using a third-party app (not officially supported by Instagram).\n\n7. **Access Direct Messages:**\n   - Click the paper plane icon in the top-right corner to access your Direct Messages (DMs).\n\n8. **Log Out:**\n   - Click your profile picture in the top-right corner, then click \"Log Out\" to sign out of your account.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for Using Instagram on Desktop:**\n- **Keyboard Shortcuts:** Use shortcuts like `J` and `K` to navigate posts, or `L` to like a post.\n- **Notifications:** Click the heart icon to see notifications.\n- **Bookmark Posts:** Save posts by clicking the bookmark icon below them.\n\n---\n\n### **Limitations of the Desktop Version:**\n- You can\u2019t upload Stories or Reels directly.\n- You can\u2019t apply filters or edit posts as easily as on the mobile app.\n- Some features (like shopping or certain creator tools) may not be fully available.\n\nIf you need full functionality, consider using the Instagram mobile app alongside the desktop version.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
